        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">Our target prediction is the closing price of the stock and graphically we seem to suspect that past data is a good predictor of future data but we wanted to do a statistical analysis with autocorrelation packages. Autocorrelation refers to the degree of correlation of the same variables between two successive time intervals. It measures how the lagged version of the value of a variable is related to the original version of it in a time series. We used a lag parameter of 100 and obtained the following strong positive correlation implying we expect good success of our predictive models:</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="image3 cid-tt612oXwA9" id="image3-5" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
