                <div class="image-wrapper"><div class="image_style" style="width:96%;"><picture><source sizes="(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" srcset="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:640/0*pNgdf3rZUgnvkiUD 640w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/0*pNgdf3rZUgnvkiUD 720w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:750/0*pNgdf3rZUgnvkiUD 750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/0*pNgdf3rZUgnvkiUD 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/0*pNgdf3rZUgnvkiUD 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/0*pNgdf3rZUgnvkiUD 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/0*pNgdf3rZUgnvkiUD 1400w" type="image/webp"/><source data-testid="og" sizes="(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" srcset="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:640/0*pNgdf3rZUgnvkiUD 640w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/0*pNgdf3rZUgnvkiUD 720w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:750/0*pNgdf3rZUgnvkiUD 750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/0*pNgdf3rZUgnvkiUD 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/0*pNgdf3rZUgnvkiUD 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/0*pNgdf3rZUgnvkiUD 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/0*pNgdf3rZUgnvkiUD 1400w"/><img alt="" loading="lazy" role="presentation" src="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:700/0*pNgdf3rZUgnvkiUD"></picture></div><br></div></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">You want the Discriminator to be good enough at its job that it does not learn simple functions but not so good that the Generator cannot fool it no matter what it learns as then it will likely not converge to good output. To accomplish this we must design a robust network with good tuning.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><h4 class="mbr-section-subtitle mbr-fonts-style mb-4 display-5">WGAN-GP as an Improved Model</h4></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">Wasserstein GAN + Gradient Penalty, or WGAN-GP, is a generative adversarial network that uses the Wasserstein loss formulation plus a gradient norm penalty to achieve Lipschitz continuity [ <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/1904.01184" target="_self">https://arxiv.org/abs/1904.01184</a> ]. This union of two results in an attempt to address weaknesses in older models.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">The Wasserstein distance (Earth Mover’s distance) is a distance metric between two probability distributions on a given metric space. Intuitively, it can be seen as the minimum work needed to transform one distribution to another. It is differentiable everywhere, which allows us to train the model to optimality and is stable enough to mostly avoid training collapse because unlike previous models where the gradient vanishes to zero if the discriminator saturates and becomes too good, this only converges as the distributions get closer, which is a meaningful result. The recently proposed Wasserstein GAN (WGAN) makes progress toward stable training of GANs, but sometimes can still generate only low-quality samples or fail to converge. Without gradient penalty this loss function utilizes weight clipping which can lead to vanishing or exploding gradients.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="image3 cid-tt612oXwA9" id="image3-5" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-12 col-lg-9">
                <div class="image-wrapper"><div class="image_style" style="width:82%;"><picture><source sizes="(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 604px" srcset="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:640/0*AI3xhnJj6TzLY9p6 640w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/0*AI3xhnJj6TzLY9p6 720w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:750/0*AI3xhnJj6TzLY9p6 750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/0*AI3xhnJj6TzLY9p6 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/0*AI3xhnJj6TzLY9p6 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/0*AI3xhnJj6TzLY9p6 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1208/0*AI3xhnJj6TzLY9p6 1208w" type="image/webp"/><source data-testid="og" sizes="(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 604px" srcset="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:640/0*AI3xhnJj6TzLY9p6 640w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/0*AI3xhnJj6TzLY9p6 720w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:750/0*AI3xhnJj6TzLY9p6 750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/0*AI3xhnJj6TzLY9p6 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/0*AI3xhnJj6TzLY9p6 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/0*AI3xhnJj6TzLY9p6 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1208/0*AI3xhnJj6TzLY9p6 1208w"/><img alt="" loading="lazy" role="presentation" src="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:604/0*AI3xhnJj6TzLY9p6"></picture></div><br></div></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">The introduction of GP is an alternative to this harsh method of clipping that instead penalizes the norm of gradient of the critic with respect to its input. This leads to a model that converges with almost all architectures and little hyperparameter tuning (though obviously better tuning leads to more stable results with less training).</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><h4 class="mbr-section-subtitle mbr-fonts-style mb-4 display-5">The Addition of GRUs</h4></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">In order to improve our model further, we want to learn from the success of LSTMs and somehow capture temporal features and locality in our learning. This is where GRUs as a replacement of normal convolutions achieve much of the gains of LSTMs with a simpler design. The GRU, known as the Gated Recurrent Unit is an RNN architecture, which is similar to LSTM units. The GRU consists of a reset gate and the update gate instead of the input, output and forget gate of the LSTM. In experimentation with convolutions, the problem of selecting good filter parameters is not an easy one. Take for example an image of a midi musical file:</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="image3 cid-tt612oXwA9" id="image3-5" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-12 col-lg-9">
                <div class="image-wrapper"><div class="image_style" style="width:96%;"><picture><source sizes="(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" srcset="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:640/0*LNaLqYuvn99oxUfK 640w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/0*LNaLqYuvn99oxUfK 720w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:750/0*LNaLqYuvn99oxUfK 750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/0*LNaLqYuvn99oxUfK 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/0*LNaLqYuvn99oxUfK 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/0*LNaLqYuvn99oxUfK 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/0*LNaLqYuvn99oxUfK 1400w" type="image/webp"/><source data-testid="og" sizes="(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" srcset="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:640/0*LNaLqYuvn99oxUfK 640w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/0*LNaLqYuvn99oxUfK 720w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:750/0*LNaLqYuvn99oxUfK 750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/0*LNaLqYuvn99oxUfK 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/0*LNaLqYuvn99oxUfK 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/0*LNaLqYuvn99oxUfK 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/0*LNaLqYuvn99oxUfK 1400w"/><img alt="" loading="lazy" role="presentation" src="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:700/0*LNaLqYuvn99oxUfK"></picture></div><br></div></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">We can see that notes have some sort of relation to the immediate surroundings but the sparseness leads to a lack of critical information at times and in that temporally a lot is encoded in the vertical dimensions. A chord of notes is as temporally close as possible but spatially on the image may be very far apart, which leads to a mismatch in this problem. Traditionally convolutions on images work quite well as you can detect the boundaries of image features easily by nearby information, but it is not generally suited to all problems.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><h4 class="mbr-section-subtitle mbr-fonts-style mb-4 display-5">How does WGAN-GP perform on Stock Predictions</h4></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">Now that we know what WGAN-GP is designed to do, we can address the problem at hand. We implemented the model described and trained it on preprocessed stock data and got the below results for prediction on training data:</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">Gains on 1000.00USD = (End Portfolio Value : 5327.83USD, Sharpe Ratio : 0.819)</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="image3 cid-tt612oXwA9" id="image3-5" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-12 col-lg-9">
