    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">It looks pretty good after 1000 training epochs. This model is not a generalist yet, but it could be with some tweaking. This is a training on one stock, the Apple stock. This is fine however as many brokerage firms would select a subset of high performing stocks to invest in and our model can easily be trained on multiple stocks, benefitting from the effects of transfer learning.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">However, when you attempt to validate on a future set of completely unseen data you get the following results:</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="image3 cid-tt612oXwA9" id="image3-5" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
