    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">For our training set on the method of using multiplying factors over the raw price we get very poor fitting changing our features into percentages of previous outputs. To clarify, if the previous price was 1USD and that entry has a multiplying factor of 1.0, the next day is 1USD. For 0.5 MF the next day is 0.5USD. For 1.5 MF the next day is 1.5USD. We transformed all features like this. In this way, we abstract away all the price specific data. This is obviously a poor result and our model manages to turn 1000.00USD into 657.90USD. <strong>I include this here, simply as a report of a failed test</strong>.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><h4 class="mbr-section-subtitle mbr-fonts-style mb-4 display-5">Implementing A Viewing Window</h4></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">It is at this point that I reexamine my core assumptions and beliefs here and I realize that the way we are training the model is different from the way we are testing the model. The inputs under training have a certain viewing window, while for testing I take this viewing window and learned geometrical attributes and throw it away. Accounting for this and instead producing a testing widow padded with historic data we end up with the following results:</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="image3 cid-tt612oXwA9" id="image3-5" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
