        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">GANs networks show promise not only in image processing, but even in the field of finances and stock predictions. These networks can be applied to even more applications than listed here. Work has been done to detect fraudulent earnings reports by detaching the discriminating portion of the network from the wider setup and using learned features to find human generated fake data as opposed to the network’s generated data. With more tuning and a bit of work in properly formatting the predictions, the results of these GANs could be stacked with a well performing regressor for even better, more resilient predictions. It is also possible to extract the entire learned latent space of the network and use this as feature inputs to a regression based model. Overall, the results of these experiments were extremely promising and warrant a more involved refinement of this application.</p></div></div></div></section><?php include_once 'Elemental/footer.php'; ?>